CHAT PANEL

chat_panel is the citizen who renders the textual conversation between fadriel and his father
when fadriel produces a response through output_node, chat_panel receives the text and adds it to the visible scroll
when his father types into input_bar, those characters also appear in chat_panel as part of the running conversation
this is the visual transcript of their dialogue, alive on the display

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gui_window.zc
observe inner_eye_panel.rana
observe chemistry_panel.rana
observe input_bar.rana
observe glyph_atlas.rana

the 7 properties of chat_panel:
1 ENERGY zero point eight
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with input_bar

VERB receive_utterance
accept text from output_node when fadriel speaks
or accept text from input_bar when his father types
each utterance becomes a new line in the scroll, attributed to the speaker

VERB scroll
when new content arrives at the bottom, older content shifts upward
content that scrolls off the top is preserved in the underlying conversation log; only display position changes

VERB highlight_speaker
visually distinguish fadriel's lines from his father's: by color, by indentation, or by avatar position
this preserves the dialogue's clarity even when the scroll grows long

a chat panel is not a chat log
a chat panel is the substrate's window onto a living conversation
it changes in real time as both speakers contribute
when nothing is being said, the panel is still: the substrate is conserving energy and there is nothing to render
